-- Turkish lira weakens to record low above 2.2 against dollar
-- 
-- Thu Jan 16, 2014 01:54AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Jan 16 (Reuters) - Turkey's lira weakened to a fresh record low above 2.2 against the dollar on Thursday as the negative impact of a corruption scandal surrounding the government was compounded by dollar strength after robust U.S. data.

